(Your result here)

TC-ST04 – Validate Conditional Visibility (Logged-in vs Logged-out)

Objective: Ensure restricted content is hidden for guests.

Steps:

1 - Open Softr site in incognito mode.

2 - Navigate through all pages.

3 - Verify that sections marked for logged-in users are hidden.

4 - Log in with a valid account.

5 - Revisit same pages.

6 - Confirm previously hidden content is now visible.

Expected Result:
Guest users do not see restricted content; logged-in users do.

Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-ST05 – Validate Form Submission (Contact Form / Custom Form)

Objective: Ensure form captures data and shows success message.

Steps:

1 - Open the form page.

2 - Click on the first field (Name) and type a valid name.

3 - Click on the Email field and type a valid email.

4 - Fill remaining fields.

5 - Click the Submit button.

6 - Observe loading indicator.

7 - Wait for success confirmation.

Refresh the page and verify:
– Form is cleared
– No duplicate submissions

Expected Result:
Form submits successfully and success message is displayed.

Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-ST06 – Validate Softr Search or Filter Functionality

Objective: Verify search/filter blocks return correct results.

Steps:

Navigate to the page containing the Search or Filter block.

Click inside the search bar.

Type a keyword that exists in database records.

Press Enter.

Observe displayed results.

Clear search.

Type a keyword that does NOT exist.

Press Enter.

Expected Result:
– Existing keyword returns correct records
– Non-existent keyword returns zero results and/or “No results found”

Actual Result:
(Your result here)
